@startuml MatchMonitorClassification_DatabaseFlow
title Match Monitor Classification - Database Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam databaseBackgroundColor #E8F5E9
skinparam databaseBorderColor #4CAF50
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #E3F2FD
skinparam activityBorderColor #1976D2

|Service Layer|
start
:ClassifyMatchMonitor Job Triggered;

|DataAccess|
:ClassifyMatchMonitor();

|CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)|
:Execute SP: **CTS_DC_CustClassification_MatchMonitor_Classify**;
note right
  **Database**: CTS_DataCenter.ctsServiceAdmin
  **Timeout**: Default
  
  **Purpose**: Get ONE match and run detection
  
  **Returns 3 ResultSets**:
  
  **ResultSet 1: ClassifyGBMMCustInfosEntity[]**
  - CustID (bigint)
  - SportGroupID (int)
  - CategoryID (int) - CC type
  - CategoryName (varchar)
  - Reason (varchar) - Detection reason
  - [Other classification fields]
  
  **ResultSet 2: MMDetailIDList (string)**
  - Comma-separated fraud ticket IDs
  - Example: "12345,67890,11111"
  - Used for marking completion
  
  **ResultSet 3: MatchID (int?)**
  - Current match being processed
  - NULL if no match in queue
  
  **Key Logic**:
  ```sql
  -- Select ONE unprocessed match (FIFO)
  SELECT TOP 1 MatchID
  FROM CTSMatchMonitor
  WHERE IsProcessed = 0
  ORDER BY ID ASC
  
  -- Run group betting detection
  -- Identify fraud tickets
  -- Extract customer info
  -- Return results
  ```
  
  **Detection Rules**:
  - Group betting patterns
  - Suspicious bet amounts
  - Related customers
  - Multi-bettype analysis
end note

:Return 3 ResultSets;

|Service Layer|
:Parse into ClassifyGBMatchMonitorModel;
note right
  **Model Structure**:
  - CustInfos (ResultSet 1)
  - MMDetailIDList (ResultSet 2)
  - MatchID (ResultSet 3)
end note

if (Has CustInfos?) then (yes)
  partition "Insert Problem Account" {
    |Service Layer|
    :Convert to InsertProblemAccountEntity[];
    
    |ProblemAccountServices|
    :InsertProblemAccountPackage();
    
    |CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)|
    :INSERT/UPDATE CTSCustomerClassification;
    note right
      **Insert/Update Customer CC**:
      
      ```sql
      INSERT INTO CTSCustomerClassification
      (CustID, CategoryID, CategoryName, 
       SportGroupID, IsPA, ...)
      VALUES (...)
      ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE
        CategoryID = VALUES(CategoryID),
        IsPA = 1,
        LastModifiedDate = NOW()
      ```
      
      **Sets**:
      - CC category (CategoryID)
      - PA flag (IsPA = 1)
      - Sport group
      - Reason for classification
    end note
    
    :Return Inserted CustIDs[];
  }
  
  partition "Push to External" {
    |Service Layer|
    :PushExternalProblemAcountPackage(CustIDs);
    
    :Batch CustIDs (500 per batch);
    
    |bodb_VR2Model (SQL Server)|
    :UPDATE MainDB Customer Classification;
    note right
      **External System Sync**:
      
      **Target**: MainDB
      **Batch Size**: 500
      
      **Update**:
      ```sql
      UPDATE CustomerClassification
      SET CategoryID = @CategoryID,
          IsPA = 1,
          UpdatedDate = GETDATE()
      WHERE CustID IN (@CustIDs)
      ```
      
      **Purpose**:
      - Sync CC status to MainDB
      - Update PA flag externally
      - Maintain data consistency
    end note
  }
endif

|Service Layer|
:ClassifyMatchMonitorCompleted(model);

|DataAccess|
if (Has MatchID?) then (yes)
  |CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)|
  :Execute SP: **CTS_DC_CustClassification_MatchMonitor_Completed**;
  note right
    **Database**: CTS_DataCenter.ctsServiceAdmin
    
    **Purpose**: Mark match as processed
    
    **Input**:
    - ip_MatchID (int) - Match that was processed
    - ip_MMDetailsIDList (string) - Fraud ticket IDs
    
    **Update Logic**:
    ```sql
    -- Parse comma-separated IDs
    CREATE TEMPORARY TABLE #TempIDs (ID INT)
    INSERT INTO #TempIDs
    SELECT value FROM STRING_SPLIT(@ip_MMDetailsIDList, ',')
    
    -- Mark tickets as processed
    UPDATE CTSMatchMonitorDetail
    SET IsProcessed = 1,
        ProcessedDate = NOW()
    WHERE ID IN (SELECT ID FROM #TempIDs)
      AND MatchID = @ip_MatchID
    
    -- Update match status
    UPDATE CTSMatchMonitor
    SET IsCompleted = 1,
        CompletedDate = NOW()
    WHERE MatchID = @ip_MatchID
    ```
    
    **Purpose**:
    - Remove from processing queue
    - Prevent duplicate processing
    - Track completion time
  end note
endif

|Service Layer|
:Complete;

note right
  **Job Completion**:
  - ONE match processed
  - Customers classified
  - Data pushed to MainDB
  - Match marked as done
  - Ready for next run
end note

stop

note right
  **Key Database Operations**:
  
  **Read Operations**:
  1. CTSMatchMonitor (SELECT unprocessed)
  2. CTSMatchMonitorDetail (SELECT fraud tickets)
  3. Detection logic queries
  
  **Write Operations**:
  1. CTSCustomerClassification (INSERT/UPDATE CC)
  2. CTSMatchMonitorDetail (UPDATE IsProcessed)
  3. CTSMatchMonitor (UPDATE IsCompleted)
  4. MainDB sync (UPDATE external)
  
  **Databases Used**:
  - CTS_DataCenter (MySQL) - Primary CTS database
  - bodb_VR2Model (SQL Server) - MainDB for external sync
  
  **Transaction Management**:
  - Each SP handles its own transaction
  - Failure in external push doesn't rollback CC insert
  - Completion marking is independent
  
  **Performance**:
  - One match at a time prevents overload
  - Batch size 500 for external push
  - Indexed on IsProcessed, MatchID
  - FIFO queue maintains order
end note

@enduml

